<p><img src="https://drive.google.com/uc?export=view&amp;id=1JMxTsHQRc2-Bdy8MhmrB21d9mKmi-wBC" alt="Image" class="center-image" /></p>

<p>The example above is similar to the rail-bed, except itâ€™s spawning instances of the top/bottom meshes stretched to each angle change, and filling the inside with wooden beams to create a dynamic fence.</p>

<p>Other things can be parametrized for systems like this one, such as the spacing of the inside pillars, pillar/rail thickness and height to give a unique look to the fencing.</p>

